{"questionId":"12397","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f'\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, 0 ≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≤ 5 is shown in the following diagram. The curve intercepts the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis at (1, 0) and (4, 0) and has a local minimum at (3, −1).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3cbb4bffa894dd2e849244395cf6acc76f04a7ec.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The shaded area enclosed by the curve <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f'\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis and the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-axis is 0.5.&nbsp;Given that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 0 \\right) = 3\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>,</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The area enclosed by the curve <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f'\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis between <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 1\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 4\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span> is 2.5 .</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>find the value of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left(&nbsp;4 \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int_1^4 {f'\\left( x \\right){\\text{d}}x}&nbsp; =&nbsp; - 2.5\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n      <mo>′</mo>\n    </msup>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>(</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>d</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2.5</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> is for −2.5.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 4 \\right) - f\\left( 1 \\right) =&nbsp; - 2.5\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2.5</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 4 \\right) = 3.5 - 2.5\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3.5</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2.5</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>=&nbsp;1 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12397","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_8c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"find the value of f ( 4 ) .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.11—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}